Pittayawat (Joe) Pittayaporn   

Department of Linguistics, faculty of Arts, Chulalongkorn University

Center of Excellence in Southeast Asian Linguistics (ChulaSEAL)

Hi, I'm Pittayawat Joe Pittayaporn, associate Professor of Linguistics at the Department of Linguistics, Chulalongkorn University My research focuses on historical linguistics and phonology, with a particular interest in the languages of Mainland Southeast Asia, especially Kra-Dai (formerly Tai-Kadai), Austroasiatic, and Mainland Austronesian languages. In phonology, I explore metrical, tonal, and prosodic phenomena, while my historical linguistic work delves into their diachronic and areal dimensions, as well as historical reconstruction and dialect subgrouping. My approach integrates theoretical perspectives with empirical data, particularly drawn from extensive fieldwork.


Updates

  • Publication: Mān on the Referentiality Continuum in Thai [with J. Kaenmuang and P. Piyamahapong]

  • Publication: Genetic variability of 23 autosomal STRs in Austroasiatic-speaking populations from Thailand [with J. Kampuansai et. al.]
